			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Syracuse N. Y.</placeName> <date>7 October 1852</date></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir&#33;</p>
				<p>In accordance to your request&#44; and deeming it<lb/> a duty&#44; I hereby tender you a report of the<lb/> proceedings of our congregation&#44; &#8220;Cheneseth Shalom&#8221;<lb/> within the late holidays.</p>
				<p>The synagogue was well attended and two<lb/> sermons were delivered by out most worthy<lb/> minister <persName>Rev. H. A. Henry</persName>&#8212;one on Bimtenhal<add>&#63;</add><lb/> <date>Sabbath</date>&#44; &#38; the other during the festival of <date>Succoth</date>.<lb/>  They were delivered in a manner which delighted<lb/> the entire audience present&#44; &#38; give great<lb/> Credit&#44; to <persName>Mr. H.</persName>  The prayers were read<lb/> on <add>Hebrew</add> and <add>Hebrew</add> by <persName>Mr H</persName> in a very<lb/> impressive style which not only satisfied the con&#61;<lb/>gregation but impressed them with a feeling<lb/> of true devotion.  The synagogue was attended<lb/> by many strangers from different parts of the<lb/> state&#44; who in concert with our members have<lb/> contributed very liberally towards the support<lb/> of the Synagogue&#44; promoted as they declared<lb/> themselves highly pleased with our <sic>procedings</sic>.&#8212;<lb/> A<add>&#63;</add> few weeks ago our highly respected President<lb/> <persName>Jacob Stone</persName> resigned&#44; whereupon <persName>Mr Isaac H Bronner</persName></p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>was elected President &#38; <persName>Mr. M. Corre<add>&#63;</add></persName><lb/> V. Pres&#58;&#59; every thing in our congregation<lb/> appears to work well towards the prosperity<lb/> knowing how happy you are to record<lb/> the deserved merits of the ministers of<lb/> our Religion I have to inform You that<lb/> our Ministers time expired on the <date>1st<lb/> of October</date>&#44; &#38; he had signified his instructions<lb/> to retire from this City&#44; having had overtures<lb/> made to him&#44; to take an other office much<lb/> more lucrative than ours&#44; and a much<lb/> larger congregation.  But such is the estimation<lb/> in which he is held by our congregation &#38;<lb/> by the unani<del>n</del>mous voice of the members<lb/> he was prevailed upon to remain among<lb/> us to which he kindly consented.</p>
				<p>The members acted <sic>jutisciarisly</sic> in their<lb/> choice&#44; convinced that the affairs of the<lb/> congregation have been materially <sic>beniffited</sic><lb/> during his administrations&#44; of which we<lb/> had sufficient proof during the late holidays.<lb/>  To show you what the feeling of the congregation<lb/> is towards <persName>Mr. H.</persName> I will say in short&#58;<lb/> that they wish to engage his services for as<lb/> long as teperiod<add>&#63;</add> as he may feel disposed&#59;<lb/> in opposition to the usual <sic>costinnes</sic> in<lb/> the states of electing minsters annually.<lb/>  I regret not to have been enabled to get</p>
			<pb n="2R"/>
				<p>any new subscribers for the Occident<lb/> I should feel obliged by your publishing<lb/> this letter if you think it worthy a<lb/> place in the next number of your magazine.</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">Yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">S Lenn</persName></p>
				<p><addressee>Isaac Leeser Esq.</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Editor of the Occident</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
				<p>PS. Haben Sie Guts<add>&#63;</add> meinen Namen<lb/> nicht ins Volle zu ziechnen sondern<lb/> nur Z. &#38; solthen Sie Schreibfehler oder<lb/> sonstige unrechte ausdr&#252;cke darin finden<lb/> so verbessern Sie es gehs und bedenken<lb/> Sie da&#223; ich in der englischen Sprache keine<lb/> so gut Fortschritte zu machen in Hande bin<lb/> als Sie es in <persName>Herrn <add>&#63;</add>ugend</persName> waren.</p>
				<p><date>Oct 11<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date>.&#44; <add>&#63;</add> sprech ich mit <add>&#63;</add><lb/> <persName>Jacob Stone</persName> welches mir sagte da&#223;<lb/> es Ihren in kurze selbst schreiben<lb/> wird<lb/> <persName>D.O.</persName></p>
		
